To add more units to the palette, simply add more objects to this templates array. For example:

```javascript
renderUnitPalette() {
    if (this.isStudentView) return;
    const c = document.getElementById('unitPalette');
    if (!c) return;
    const templates = [
        // Safety Units
        { code: 'AHCWHS302', name: 'Work Health & Safety', color: 'safety', tags: ['SAFETY'] },
        { code: 'HLTAID011', name: 'First Aid', color: 'safety', tags: ['SAFETY'] },
        
        // Foundational Units
        { code: 'AHCBIO303', name: 'Biosecurity', color: 'foundational', tags: [] },
        { code: 'AHCNSY207', name: 'Propagation activities', color: 'foundational', tags: [] },
        { code: 'AHCFAU302', name: 'Identify fauna', color: 'foundational', tags: ['SEASONAL'] },
        { code: 'AHCPCM303', name: 'Identify plant specimens', color: 'foundational', tags: [] },
        
        // Practical Units
        { code: 'AHCPMG301', name: 'Control weeds', color: 'practical', tags: [] },
        { code: 'AHCCHM304', name: 'Transport chemicals', color: 'practical', tags: ['SPECIALIST'] },
        { code: 'AHCCHM307', name: 'Apply chemicals', color: 'practical', tags: ['SPECIALIST'] },
        { code: 'FWPCOT2266', name: 'Operate brush cutter', color: 'practical', tags: ['SPECIALIST'] },
        { code: 'AHCECR301', name: 'Maintain ecosystems', color: 'practical', tags: [] },
        { code: 'AHCLPW313', name: 'Water sampling', color: 'practical', tags: ['SEASONAL'] },
        
        // Machinery Units
        { code: 'AHCMOM213', name: 'Operate chainsaw', color: 'machinery', tags: ['SPECIALIST'] },
        { code: 'AHCMOM216', name: 'Operate SSUV', color: 'machinery', tags: ['SPECIALIST'] },
        
        // Seasonal Units
        { code: 'AHCECR305', name: 'Collect native seed', color: 'seasonal', tags: ['SEASONAL'] },
        
        // Apex/Project Units
        { code: 'AHCECR309', name: 'Ecological site inspection', color: 'apex', tags: ['APEX'] },
        { code: 'INTEGRATION', name: 'Skill Integration', color: 'project', tags: [] },
        { code: 'PROJECT', name: 'Final Project Phase', color: 'project', tags: [] },
        
        // Assessment
        { code: 'ASSESSMENT', name: '📋 Assessment Task', color: 'assessment', tags: ['ASSESSMENT'] },
        
        // Custom
        { code: 'CUSTOM', name: 'Custom Unit', color: 'foundational', tags: ['CUSTOM'] }
    ];
    // ... rest of the method remains the same
}
```

Key points:

· Each template object needs: code, name, color, and tags properties
· The color should match one of the existing color keys: safety, foundational, practical, machinery, apex, project, specialist, seasonal, assessment
· Tags are used for filtering/highlighting (e.g., SAFETY, SPECIALIST, SEASONAL, APEX, ASSESSMENT)
· These units will appear in the left sidebar and can be dragged onto the timeline

The units you add here will be available in the drag-and-drop palette. They will automatically use the appropriate colors from your existing color mapping system.
